SIMPLE: twirl
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Twirl
<hw>Twirl</hw> <pr>(tw⟦etil⟧rl)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Twirled</conjf>
<pr>(tw⟦etil⟧rld)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Twirling</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf. AS. <ets>⟦thorn⟧wiril</ets>
a churn staff, a stirrer, flail, <ets>⟦thorn⟧weran</ets>,
<ets>⟦amac⟧⟦thorn⟧weran</ets>, to agitate, twirl, G. <ets>zwirlen</ets>,
<ets>quirlen</ets>, <ets>querlen</ets> to twirl, to turn round or about,
<ets>quirl</ets> a twirling stick, OHG. <ets>dweran</ets> to twirl,
stir. Cf. <er>Trowel</er>.]</ety> <def>To move or turn round rapidly; to
whirl round; to move and turn rapidly with the fingers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>See ruddy maids,⟦br⟧
Some taught with dexterous hand to <qex>twirl</qex> the wheel.</q>
<rj><qau>Dodsley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>No more beneath soft eve's consenting star⟦br⟧
Fandango <qex>twirls</qex> his jocund castanet.</q>
<rj><qau>Byron.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Twirl</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Twirl
<hw>Twirl</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To revolve with velocity; to be
whirled round rapidly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Twirl</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Twirl
<hw>Twirl</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of twirling; a
rapid circular motion; a whirl or whirling; quick rotation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A twist; a convolution.</def>
<rj><au>Woodward.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Twist</ent>⟦br⟧
